<inglise> 78/685/EEC: Commission Decision of 26 July 1978 establishing a list of epizootic diseases in accordance with Directive 72/462/EEC </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS nr 78/685/EM&Uuml; episootiliste haiguste loetelu koostamise kohta vastavalt direktiivile 72/462/EM&Uuml; 26. juuli 1978 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 72/462/EEC of 12 December 1972 on health and veterinary inspection problems upon importation of bovine animals and swine and fresh meat from third countries (1), and in particular Articles 12 (3) (c) and 29 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 12. detsembri 1972. aasta direktiivi 72/462/EM&Uuml; tervishoiu ja veterinaarinspektsiooni probleemide kohta veiste, sigade ja v&auml;rske liha impordil kolmandatest riikidest, (1) eriti selle artikli 12 l&otilde;ike 3 punkti c ja artiklit 29, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it may be necessary to proceed with the slaughter and destruction of all animals of a consignment which on arrival in the territory of the Community shows evidence or suspicion of an epizootic disease, in particular those which are exotic for the Community, in order to safeguard the health of man and animals and to avoid the very serious consequences which may result from the appearance or development of such diseases within the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: v&otilde;ib osutuda vajalikuks tappa ja h&auml;vitada k&otilde;ik partii loomad, eelk&otilde;ige &uuml;henduses eksootilised, kui neil on &uuml;henduse territooriumile j&otilde;udes episootilise haiguse tundem&auml;rke v&otilde;i kui nad &auml;ratavad sellekohast kahtlust, et kaitsta inimese ja loomade tervist ja hoida &auml;ra v&auml;ga raskeid tagaj&auml;rgi, mis v&otilde;ivad tuleneda selle haiguse ilmnemisest v&otilde;i levimisest &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measure provided for in this Decision is in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Veterinary Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva otsusega etten&auml;htud meede on koosk&otilde;las alalise veterinaarkomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> All animals in a consignment presented for importation may be slaughtered and destroyed, when the health inspection carried out on the arrival of the animals in the territory of the Community in accordance with Article 12 (1) of Directive 72/462/EEC, shows evidence or suspicion of one of the epizootic diseases on the list figuring in the Annex hereto. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik importimiseks esitatud partii loomad v&otilde;ib tappa ja h&auml;vitada, kui loomadele &uuml;henduse territooriumile saabudes vastavalt direktiivi 72/462/EM&Uuml; artikli 12 l&otilde;ikele 1 tehtud tervishoiukontroll n&auml;itab &uuml;he k&auml;esoleva otsuse lisas loetletud episootilise haiguse esinemist v&otilde;i sellekohast kahtlust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 26 July 1978. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 26. juuli 1978 </eesti>
